Vice President Kamala Harris met with Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India to strengthen the strategic partnership between the United States and India. They discussed various topics, including the COVID-19 pandemic and efforts to respond and recover. This includes cooperation on vaccine production under the Quad Vaccine Partnership. Harris commended India's commitment to resume vaccine exports and the progress of its domestic vaccination campaign.

Both leaders agreed on the importance of taking ambitious action to combat climate change in the face of the climate crisis. They also emphasized their commitment to democratic values and discussed the need to strengthen democracy both at home and abroad.

They expressed support for expanding bilateral security cooperation to address modern threats such as terrorism and cybercrime. As the chair of the National Space Council, Harris encouraged increased U.S.-India space cooperation. They also explored ways to enhance existing bilateral collaboration on space.